Description: Near Bermuda Run / Mile Marker 180 to 182 Both Directions. The Contractor for the&nbsp;I-40 Project at the Davie/Forsyth County Line is scheduled to close both directions of I-40 between NC 801 (Exit 180) and Harper Road (Exit 182) during the overnight hours of Monday March 22nd. On Monday March 22nd the contractor will begin installing lane closures on I-40 at 6:00 PM and a full road closure of I-40 will be installed beginning at 11:00 PM. Detours will be utilized&nbsp;for this&nbsp;road closure with all I-40 Eastbound traffic exiting at NC 801 (Exit 180) and all I-40 Westbound traffic exiting at Harper Road (Exit 182). Detoured traffic will use NC 801 US 158 and Harper Road.&nbsp;All lanes of I-40 are expected to be reopened to traffic by 6:00 AM Tuesday March 23rd.&nbsp;This closure is required for the contractor to safely place the concrete deck for the new pedestrian bridge over I-40. As always this work is weather dependent and may be subject to change.
